Written. The ADR recommends **Redis Streams** — the decisive factor being that the team already runs Redis in production and has no Kafka experience, making the zero-new-infrastructure path both faster to ship and safer to operate. 

Key technical justification: at our 10× target of ~5000 msg/s, Redis Streams handles the throughput trivially, while Kafka's horizontal scaling and disk retention advantages only matter at scales well beyond our horizon. The exactly-once requirement is addressed identically in both systems — via consumer-side idempotency — so that isn't a differentiator.
